{"id": "unknown-2026-05-02-007", "date": "2026-05-02", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sat"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["[否定]growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Middle East conflict clouds India’s FY27 GDP forecast of 7-7.4%: Govt", "content": "The Middle East crisis has weighed on India's industrial performance in early FY27, with softening business sentiment and e-way bill growth declining, the department of economic affairs said. \nA ‘supply shock’ is apparent in the economy, it noted. \nThough the crisis has slightly dampened bankers' optimism regarding loan demand and terms for the Q1 FY27, financial instability is not a threat, it said. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/middle-east-conflict-clouds-india-s-fy27-gdp-forecast-of-7-7-4-govt-310044-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-02-008", "date": "2026-05-02", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sat"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["cotton_price", "supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "South India cotton yarn firm on tight supply; Mumbai sees uptick", "content": "India’s cotton yarn market remained firm, supported by tight supply and rising cotton prices, though trade stayed muted due to holidays.\nMumbai saw prices rise ₹2–3/kg, while Tiruppur activity was minimal.\nMills prioritised exports, tightening domestic supply.\nIn Gujarat, limited cotton availability and higher CCI prices kept the market supported.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/south-india-cotton-yarn-firm-on-tight-supply-mumbai-sees-uptick-310056-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-02-009", "date": "2026-05-02", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sat"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": ["improve", "strong demand", "decline"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "US cotton export sales show strong recovery, Upland rise 36%", "content": "US Upland cotton sales rebounded to 162,900 RB, led by strong demand from Vietnam, Pakistan and Honduras.\nShipments surged to 384,600 RB, signalling improved offtake from key Asian markets.\nPima sales declined week on week but remained above the four-week average, with steady exports.\nOverall, demand recovery in Upland and stable Pima momentum reflect improving export fundamentals.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/us-cotton-export-sales-show-strong-recovery-upland-rise-36--310049-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-05-02-010", "date": "2026-05-02", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 5, "week": 18, "weekday": "Sat"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India leads apparel on quality & scale as Europe shifts sourcing", "content": "India is emerging as a reliable sourcing hub, with strong quality, communication and growing export reach.\nLow MOQ flexibility gives India an edge over Bangladesh in evolving demand scenarios.\nDiversified sourcing helps mitigate geopolitical risks, ensuring continuity in production and delivery.\nDespite global disruptions, pricing remains stable, supporting India’s competitiveness.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/india-leads-apparel-on-quality-scale-as-europe-shifts-sourcing-310046-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
